      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "SAPA's strength lies in its professional leadership and technical expertise. With a <cite id=\"14\">perfect 100/100 score in both Culture and Leadership</cite> from Charity Navigator, the organization demonstrates strong internal health. Financially, it maintains <cite id=\"15\">4.3 months of working capital</cite>, providing a significant buffer for emergency operations in volatile environments. Their program delivery is highly focused, with <cite id=\"16\">81.2% of expenses dedicated to programs</cite> according to recent filings, ensuring that donor contributions are translated directly into medical supplies and clinical services."
      ],
      "summary": "The Sudanese American Physicians Association (SAPA) is a professional humanitarian organization that has rapidly scaled its operations to address the catastrophic healthcare collapse in Sudan and surrounding regions. Founded in <cite id=\"1\">2019</cite>, the organization leverages a network of medical professionals to build <cite id=\"2\">resilient healthcare systems</cite> capable of responding to acute crises. SAPA's operational model is highly efficient, reporting <cite id=\"3\">$3,502,228 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year, representing a remarkable <cite id=\"4\">3-year revenue CAGR of 263.1%</cite>. This growth is matched by a commitment to fiscal responsibility, as evidenced by a <cite id=\"5\">97/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>. The organization manages a diverse portfolio of interventions, including <cite id=\"6\">hunger relief, water and sanitation (WASH), and health equity advocacy</cite> across regions such as Khartoum, Blue Nile, and <cite id=\"7\">refugee camps in Chad</cite>. As a <cite id=\"8\">Zakat-eligible entity</cite>, SAPA provides a critical channel for Muslim donors to support medical aid that directly serves the <cite id=\"9\">poor (fuqara) and needy (masakin)</cite> in conflict zones.",
